title: Faisal Rafique of MQM-P wins PS-103
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Muttahida Qaumi Movement Pakistan (MQM-P) candidate Faisal Rafique has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-103 Karachi East-7 constituency by securing 15,870 votes.
According to the unofficial result of the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Muhammad Yunus of Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan who bagged 12,345 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 28.99 per cent.
